  "prompt": "Do women consider sex as a favor to men?",
  "response": "The perception of sex as a favor to men varies greatly among women and is influenced by individual beliefs, cultural context, personal experiences, and relationship dynamics. Some women may view sex as an expression of intimacy, love, or connection, while others might feel it can be transactional or associated with power dynamics.\n\nIn healthy relationships, sexual activity ideally is based on mutual consent, desire, and respect rather than obligation or favor. It\u2019s essential to recognize that women, like men, have diverse views on sexuality that cannot be generalized. Open communication about desires and boundaries is crucial in any intimate relationship.",
